A backslash immediately before a key path delimiter (``\.`` ``\[`` ``\]`` ``\=``) now escapes that character rather than being treated as a literal backslash followed by an active delimiter. This affects only the rare case of keys whose names end with a backslash: ``OmegaConf.select(cfg, r"a\.b")`` previously navigated to key ``"a\"`` then ``"b"``; it now resolves to the single key ``"a.b"``. Keys ending in a backslash are not idiomatic in YAML and this change is unlikely to be encountered in practice.
